      {
        "content": "Social media platforms systematically exploit user data, often without explicit consent, raising significant privacy concerns. These platforms track, store, and analyze personal information to create detailed profiles that are then sold to advertisers, undermining individual autonomy and control over personal data. This pervasive surveillance not only erodes privacy but also exposes users to risks such as identity theft and manipulation through targeted misinformation. Inadequate privacy safeguards and opaque data handling practices necessitate urgent reforms to ensure transparency and empower users with greater control over their personal information, safeguarding fundamental privacy rights in an increasingly digital world.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
