        "content": "While social media does offer connectivity and support, the underlying issues of mental health cannot be overlooked or mitigated by mere surface-level features. The platforms' existing measures, such as content warnings and usage tracking, are often insufficient and reactive, failing to address the systemic nature of the problem. The algorithms that prioritize engagement continue to thrive on negative content, exacerbating mental health concerns. Without substantial reform focusing on algorithmic accountability and ethical design, social media's adverse impact on mental health will persist, overshadowing its potential benefits and harming users' psychological well-being.",
